segment.source: To set advanced file transfer options
segment.target: To set advanced file transfer options

segment.source: In the Deployment pane, click Advanced.
segment.target: In the Deployment pane, click Advanced.

segment.source: In the File Transfer Options dialog box, configure the parameters as described in the following table.
segment.target: In the File Transfer Options dialog box, configure the parameters as described in the following table.

segment.source: Click OK.
segment.target: Click OK.

segment.source: Run command on received files
segment.target: Run command on received files

segment.source: Select this check box to run a command line on all files transferred to the host.
segment.target: Select this check box to run a command line on all files transferred to the host.

segment.source: In the command-line box, enter the command line to run on all received files.
segment.target: In the command-line box, enter the command line to run on all received files.

segment.source: File types
segment.target: File types

segment.source: Allow all file extensions—Click to enable transferring files of any file name extension from the MED-V workspace to the host.
segment.target: Allow all file extensions—Click to enable transferring files of any file name extension from the MED-V workspace to the host.

segment.source: Allow the following file extensions—Click to enable only files with specified file name extensions to be transferred.
segment.target: Allow the following file extensions—Click to enable only files with specified file name extensions to be transferred.

segment.source: In the empty field, enter all file name extensions allowed, separated by commas.
segment.target: In the empty field, enter all file name extensions allowed, separated by commas.
